news.summary: Apple  CEO Tim Cook bought nearly $3 million shares of depressed  Nike  stock following the company’s disappointing earnings report last week.  Cook, who is the lead independent director of Nike and a board member since 2005, bought 50,000 shares of Nike stock on Monday at an average price of $58.97, according to a form 4 filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission late Tuesday.  Cook now holds just over 105,000 shares of the footwear maker.
